{"change_summary":"Refactored `src/adapters/process_backend.rs` so failure handling uses a dedicated `cleanup_failed_invocation()` path instead of preserving artifacts and then calling normal cleanup. Non-zero exits and post-run parse/read failures now move Codex temp files into `runtime/failed/`, write a `<invocation_id>.failed.raw` file with combined stdout/stderr, and avoid deleting the original temp files if the move itself fails. Normal successful cleanup still removes temp files. Added unit coverage for successful failure-artifact preservation, failed-move preservation fallback, and normal success cleanup.","outstanding_risks":["Did not run a full end-to-end backend invocation; validation was limited to targeted `process_backend` tests under `nix-shell` because `cargo` is not available on PATH in this environment."],"steps":[{"description":"Inspect current `process_backend.rs` invoke/cleanup behavior to confirm where failed backend exits were still followed by normal temp-file deletion.","order":0,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Refactor failure cleanup to preserve Codex schema/last-message artifacts and `.failed.raw` output without a follow-up delete, and update all relevant error paths to use it.","order":1,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Add focused tests for failed-artifact preservation, failed move fallback, and normal success cleanup behavior.","order":2,"status":"completed"}],"validation_evidence":["`nix-shell -p cargo rustc --run 'cargo test cleanup_failed_invocation -- --nocapture'` passed: 2 tests passed, 0 failed.","`nix-shell -p cargo rustc --run 'cargo test cleanup_deletes_codex_temp_files_on_success -- --nocapture'` passed: 1 test passed, 0 failed.","`nix-shell -p cargo rustc --run 'cargo test adapters::process_backend::tests -- --nocapture'` passed: 26 tests passed, 0 failed."]}